Q1 — NEEDS_REVISION. Process topology confused: “supervisor spawns Rust gateway + Python dispatcher pair” vs Q2 “Python gateway connects to Rust supervisor IPC.” Fix: one Rust `agentd` supervisor hosts transports + IPC server, spawns Python gateway/dispatcher child only. Status writer in supervisor. LaunchAgent/systemd wrapper starts `makakoo agentd --slot <slot>`.

Q2 — NEEDS_REVISION. Python may do defense-in-depth, but cannot be authoritative for tool/path scope. Fix: Rust MCP/grant layer enforces final scope; Python preflights only. Audit violations in Rust source-of-truth path.

Q3 — NEEDS_REVISION. Archive path violates repo rule: never touch `~/.makakoo/archive`. Fix archive to `$MAKAKOO_HOME/archive/agents/<slot>-<ts>/`. Also `--yes` must not auto-revoke secrets; keep secrets unless `--revoke-secrets` explicit. Slot.toml scan is weak; use secret ref index or conservative “maybe shared” handling.

Q4 — LOCKED. Precedence sane. Add validation that model id exists in configured AIL registry; unknown model fails `agent validate`, not at runtime.

Q5 — LOCKED. Add explicit raw-body HMAC verification + timestamp replay check before JSON parse. Otherwise shape good.

Q6 — NEEDS_REVISION. `MESSAGE_CONTENT` is privileged and may fail for normal users. Fix: support degraded mode: DMs always, guild mentions/buttons/slash-command style without content intent where possible; validate intent availability separately.

Q7 — LOCKED. Cloud API only is right. Ensure webhook verification includes Meta `hub.challenge` GET flow plus POST signature over raw body.

Q8 — NEEDS_REVISION. `account_id = mailbox local-part` collides across domains. Fix: account_id = full normalized mailbox address. Also “strip quoted replies aggressively” risks data loss; keep raw body in metadata/audit-debug, send stripped text to LLM.

Q9 — NEEDS_REVISION. Flow impossible as written: Twilio recording-complete webhook cannot return TwiML `<Play>` to same already-ended request reliably. Fix: use `<Gather>/<Record>` loop with callback URL that returns next TwiML, or outbound call update API. Lock exact call-state machine before implementation.

Q10 — NEEDS_REVISION. “Ed25519-signed cookie” over random visitor id is overkill/awkward; use HMAC/AEAD app secret unless repo already has Ed25519 key infra. Also Secure cookie breaks localhost demo unless special-case dev. Fix: prod Secure=true, localhost dev exception.

Q11 — LOCKED. Good harness. Add “no real transport credentials/network” invariant; all scenarios mock-only unless explicit dogfood flag.

Q12 — NEEDS_REVISION. `RLIMIT_AS = 512MB` will break Python/LLM deps on macOS unpredictably; `RLIMIT_NPROC` macOS caveat already known. Fix: configurable per slot, default soft observe/warn first or higher default; hard enforce only after measured baseline. Slot cap 32 locked.

Q13 — LOCKED. Inbound-only token bucket sane. Add transport-level bypass for provider verification/challenge webhooks so Slack/Meta verification cannot be rate-limited.

Q14 — NEEDS_REVISION. Logging `secret.resolve` can leak secret names/targets if detail sloppy. Fix schema: never log secret values; detail is typed redacted object. Also 100MB rotation needs total cap from R9 in Q14 itself, not only risk table.

